# QIP significance nudge

This rule does not define the workflow. It only nudges agents to invoke `qv-arch-qip-significance-check` when appropriate.

## When to invoke

During planning, implementation, or PR review, invoke `qv-arch-qip-significance-check` when a change clearly affects stable contracts, package boundaries, native/platform support, runtime/transport/storage choices, published NFRs, architecture principles, or delivery architecture in CI.

## When not to invoke

Do not invoke for ordinary refactors, localized bug fixes, routine tests, documentation edits, or CI maintenance such as cache tuning, matrix cleanup, or flaky-test fixes unless they change one of the behaviors above.

## Outcome

The skill recommends creating a QIP. It is advisory only and must not block work mechanically.
